Wanted to celebrate #SmallBusinessSaturday and National Entrepreneurs Day by giving @monicadianehammond a shout out.

Monica quit on me . . . and I couldn't be happier.

In 2009, Monica started working for me as an intern on Awesome 80s Prom. And I'll never forget the day I saw her scurrying around the office with a determined look on her face for a very minor task. "Anyone who takes her internship this seriously, is going to be a force to reckon with someday." I promoted her almost immediately and she ended up as my Marketing Director.  And more importantly, a friend.  And it's why I entrusted her with @theatermakersstudio which I founded and she helped build . . . and now she runs!

But that's not all.  She's an entrepreneur who owns and runs not 1, not 2, but FOUR companies (one of which helps OTHER small businesses). 

Kudos to her and to all the small business founders out there . . . including all you theatermakers. Whether you're an Off-Broadway show or an actor or director . . . you are a small business!  And if you think like you're a business owner, you'll be a BIG business before you know it.

